Detailed Description

Contain all the data about an item on the map.

An item is e.g. a piece of an street (like street_rec in OldMapCentral), a forest, a lake.

void OldItem::setGfxData (  GfxDataFull *  gfx,
bool  deleteOld = false
) 
 

Set the geographical representation to a new value.

NB! The given gfxData is not copied, and must therefore not be deleted by the caller.

Warning:
The old GfxData will not be deleted since it might be allocated by an allocator in the map. Sa if the old GfxData is allocated elsewhere this might introduce a memory leak.
Parameters:
gfx The new gfxData that have the georaphical information about this item.

virtual bool OldItem::updateAttributesFromItem (  OldItem *  otherItem,
bool  sameMap = true
)  [virtual]
 

Virtual method that updates all attributes of item and, if any, its nodes and connections to the values of the other item.

This includes e.g. names, groups, entry restrictions, sign posts, speed limit and gfxdata.

If the items originates from different maps, typically one underview and one overview or country overview map, the sameMap param should be set to false. In this case some attributes can not be updated by the item itself; names and sign post names (depending on string index), connections (depending on underview- and overview fromNodeIds). Update of these attributes is then taken care of in the overview- and country overview maps where id lookup tables and the map string tables are known. Note that group ids are updated here even if the item originates from different maps; updating to e.g. overview ids must then be handled separately.

Parameters:
otherItem The item from which to get update values.
sameMap Default true meaning that the items are one and the same (same map), set to false if the items originates from different maps (e.g. underview and overview map)
Returns:
True if some attribute was updated for the item, false if not.

Reimplemented in OldAirportItem, OldBuildingItem, OldBuiltUpAreaItem, OldCartographicItem, OldCityPartItem, OldFerryItem, OldForestItem, OldIndividualBuildingItem, OldIslandItem, OldMunicipalItem, OldParkItem, OldPointOfInterestItem, OldRailwayItem, OldRouteableItem, OldStreetItem, OldStreetSegmentItem, OldWaterItem, OldZipAreaItem, and OldZipCodeItem.

uint32 OldItem::m_localID [protected]
 

The local id of this item.

The first bit (bit 0) is used for identify node0 or node1 (this means that the first bit is unused for every item except for the subclass "OldStreetSegmentItem"). Bit 1 to 4 shows on what zoomlevel this item is significant.
